messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hi.
This is a 911 emergency operator on Molokai.
Hello?
Yeah.
I'm in a white Honda, and my car doesn't want to turn off.
Okay, and your brakes?
The car doesn't want to stop.
You can't turn off your car. Can you put it in neutral?
It can't come out of gear.
Okay, and you can't put it in neutral?
No.
Where are you at?
I'm heading towards town. Just passed the rubbish dump.
Okay, a white Honda heading towards town past the rubbish dump.
I'm losing control.
Alright, who am I talking to?
Gage.
Gage, is there any way you can turn off the car or put it in neutral? Is it automatic?
It's standard. I can't kick it into neutral.
Can you push in your clutch?
I can, but my gear is stuck.
Okay, push in your clutch. You should be able to slow down.
It's not slowing down.
You've got your clutch in and your brake on, and it's still not slowing down?
Yeah, it's still not slowing down.
Where are you now?
I just saw a cop. I'm losing control. My car is swerving.
Keep trying to put it in neutral. They're coming your way.
I can't stop. I'm going to crash.
Have you tried your parking brake?
It's not working. I can't stop.
Your brakes are on, but the car still isn't stopping?
No, it won't stop.
Okay, stay on the line.
Hello? Hello?
Are you okay?
